OE PROGRAM 8

AWS Auto Scaling

Aim
To automatically scale EC2 instances.

Step 1 Open EC2

1. Open EC2 dashboard.
2. Open Auto Scaling Groups.

Step 2 Create Launch Template

1. Click Create Launch Template.
2. Select AMI.
3. Select instance type.
4. Save template.

Step 3 Create Auto Scaling Group

1. Click Create Auto Scaling Group.
2. Select launch template.
3. Select VPC.
4. Select subnets.

Step 4 Configure Scaling

1. Enter minimum maximum and desired instances.
2. Attach load balancer.
3. Configure scaling policy.

Result
AWS Auto Scaling configured successfully.

